mj-section(padding="35px 40px 40px 40px" mj-class="bgBf")
    mj-column(width="100%" padding-bottom="25px")
        mj-text(padding="0" align="center" mj-class="T28-500" color="#FFFFFF") Benefits of the Malta residency program
    mj-column(width="100%" padding-bottom="20px")
        mj-text(padding="0" mj-class="T16-400" color="#CDC5C5") In addition to being a fairly quick path to residency - just six to eight months for approval - there are many other benefits to this highly sought-after program:
    mj-group(width="100%")
        mj-column(width="5%" padding-bottom="15px")
            mj-text(padding="0" mj-class="T30-500 cR") +
        mj-column(width="95%" padding-bottom="15px")
            mj-text(padding="0" mj-class="T16-400" color="#CDC5C5") Residence in an EU country with visa-free access across Europe's Schengen Area for 90 days out of a 180-day period.
    mj-group(width="100%")
        mj-column(width="5%" padding-bottom="15px")
            mj-text(padding="0" mj-class="T30-500 cR") +
        mj-column(width="95%" padding-bottom="15px")
            mj-text(padding="0" mj-class="T16-400" color="#CDC5C5") The right to reside indefinitely in Malta (one of Europe's safest countries).
    mj-group(width="100%")
        mj-column(width="5%" padding-bottom="15px")
            mj-text(padding="0" mj-class="T30-500 cR") +
        mj-column(width="95%" padding-bottom="15px")
            mj-text(padding="0" mj-class="T16-400" color="#CDC5C5") Investment required for the first five years only (and only after you have secured approval).
    mj-group(width="100%")
        mj-column(width="5%" padding-bottom="15px")
            mj-text(padding="0" mj-class="T30-500 cR") +
        mj-column(width="95%" padding-bottom="15px")
            mj-text(padding="0" mj-class="T16-400" color="#CDC5C5") Family members can be included.
    mj-group(width="100%")
        mj-column(width="5%" padding-bottom="15px")
            mj-text(padding="0" mj-class="T30-500 cR") +
        mj-column(width="95%" padding-bottom="15px")
            mj-text(padding="0" mj-class="T16-400" color="#CDC5C5") No residence requirement to maintain your permanent residence status.
    mj-group(width="100%")
        mj-column(width="5%" padding-bottom="55px")
            mj-text(padding="0" mj-class="T30-500 cR") +
        mj-column(width="95%" padding-bottom="55px")
            mj-text(padding="0" mj-class="T16-400" color="#CDC5C5") English is the official language - and there is no language test.
    mj-column(width="100%")
        mj-text(padding="0" mj-class="T16-400" color="#CDC5C5") Once you receive approval, your permanent residency card is issued with a five-year validity (and easily renewed every five years with a new photo).
